description: Defence minister Rajnath Singh emphasized the Indian Navy's role as a peace guarantor in the Indian Ocean Region while laying the foundation for a VLF radar station in Vikarabad, Telangana. He stressed maritime security as a collective effort and highlighted potential local benefits like job opportunities and infrastructure development.

description: Over 17 years after confessing to her husband's murder, Laulina Achariya's life sentence is overturned by the Orissa High Court due to trial court errors and lack of proper evidence analysis, marking a major instance of miscarriage of justice.

description: The Supreme Court has questioned the recruitment of civic volunteers under West Bengal's 'Ratirer Sathi' scheme, following a rape-murder incident involving a volunteer. The court barred their deployment in hospitals and schools, seeking details from the state on the recruitment process within three weeks.

description: Union Home Minister Amit Shah addresses IPS probationers, urging them to adopt a ruthless approach towards anti-national activities. Shah highlights progress in reducing violence in previously troubled regions and the importance of police in securing citizen rights. Emphasizes technological advancements and new laws for timely justice.

description: UP government plans a new law to prevent food contamination by requiring food outlets to disclose essential information about staff. Establishments must display signboards, have staff wear ID badges, and install CCTV cameras. Strict action is proposed against personnel providing false information or illegal foreign nationals. Food handlers will also need to adhere to strict hygiene rules.

description: The Election Commission has enlarged the symbol size of Sharad Pawar's NCP faction on EVMs for better visibility. description: The Mahayuti alliance faces a crucial election in Maharashtra on Nov 20, following a poor performance in the LS polls. Major issues include farmer distress, unemployment, and caste-based demands. The BJP aims to retain power amidst internal splits and opposition gains.

description: Congress general secretary Priyanka Gandhi Vadra is set to make her electoral debut in the bypoll for Kerala's Wayanad Lok Sabha seat on November 13, replacing brother Rahul Gandhi. The seat was vacated as Rahul chose to retain Rae Bareli in Uttar Pradesh.

description: Protests by Maratha, OBC, and Dhangar communities in Marathwada are influencing voting patterns. The BJP-led Mahayuti faces significant challenges, with internal tensions and quota disputes threatening its prospects. Prominent activists push for specific quota solutions, impacting both Mahayuti and MVA political strategies.

Seat-sharing remains a complex issue for both alliances, with key parties negotiating candidacies to maximize their electoral chances.

Congress spokesperson Rashid Alvi had urged for paper ballots, citing the PM's ties with Israel. BJP dismissed these claims, attributing such accusations to Congress's political desperation.

description: Election Commission criticizes exit polls for lack of scientific basis and transparency, and warns against creating false expectations. Chief Election Commissioner Rajiv Kumar highlighted the mismatch between early media trends and actual results, urging introspection and self-regulation by broadcasters and pollsters to ensure accurate reporting.

description: In a rare diplomatic interaction, India's Foreign Minister S Jaishankar shook hands with Pakistani PM Shehbaz Sharif at the SCO meeting in Islamabad. No formal bilateral talks were scheduled, focusing instead on SCO's trade and economic agenda. Possible bilateral engagement remains uncertain.

description: The Indian Patent Office has rejected Viiv Healthcare's patent application for the HIV drug, dolutegravir, after nearly a decade of legal battles. This decision opens the market for generic versions, promoting affordable access to treatment and potentially reducing costs. The ruling addresses concerns over 'evergreening' practices in patent filings.

description: As the video of Donald Trump standing on the stage doing nothing went viral, Trump supporters claimed that the Kamala Harris campaign doctored the video as desperate measures while Trump actually decided to play music for the town hall after there were two medical emergencies. description: Due to heavy rains and an orange alert, the Karnataka government has advised Bengaluru's IT, BT, and private firms to let employees work from home on October 16 for safety reasons. Jaishankar visited Pakistan for the first time in nearly nine years, meeting Prime Minister Shehbaz Sharif during an informal dinner ahead of the SCO Council of Heads of Government meeting. Proponents of the conspiracy have pointed to vague timelines and photographs to support their claims. However, these arguments fall apart under scrutiny. Justin Trudeau was born on December 25, 1971, more than four years before Margaret and Pierre Trudeau, the then-Canadian Prime Minister, made an official visit to Cuba, where they first met Castro.

title: 'Israel will listen to US, but ...': Netanyahu's office issues statement

description: Vivian Dsena's caring nature towards Shrutika Raaj on Bigg Boss 18 is admired by fans and co-star Twinkle Arora. Even his wife, Nouran Aly, appreciated their bond. Shrutika recently addressed an issue of being mocked for her South Indian accent by Alice Kaushik, emphasizing the difference between mocking and good-natured teasing.
title: BB18: Vivian's wife reacts to Shrutika and his cute bond; writes 'love this...'

description: Following a recent injection of funds, SpiceJet has been removed from the DGCA's enhanced surveillance. The airline had been monitored closely due to financial issues impacting maintenance. While improvements have been noted, the DGCA will continue to conduct random spot checks to ensure ongoing safety.
title: SpiceJet off DGCA enhanced surveillance list but random checks to continue

description: Bharti Airtel's Sunil Mittal advocated for satellite companies to follow the same rules as telecom operators, including purchasing spectrum and paying license fees.
title: Bharti Airtel chairman Sunil Mittal supports this Reliance Jio demand

description: The Tata Group plans to transfer 17 Airbus A320 Neo aircraft from Air India and 10 from Vistara to expand Air India Express's all-economy fleet. This restructuring aims to compete with market leader Indigo and will conclude by mid-2025.
title: How Tatas plan to take on Indigo in low-cost airline category

description: The Supreme Court sought responses from the Centre and the Election Commission on a petition challenging the practice of political parties promising freebies during campaigns, arguing it burdens the public exchequer and lacks accountability. The petition connects this practice to bribery and constitutional violations.
title: SC issues notice to Centre, EC on pleas against promise of freebies

description: A 29-year-old homemaker in Bengaluru allegedly killed her two young daughters before taking her own life. Her husband, Avinash, hanged himself upon discovering their bodies. Police suspect a marital dispute or financial pressure may have driven the tragic event. An investigation and postmortem reports are awaited to uncover more details.
title: Bengaluru horror: Mom kills two girls and hangs self, spouse ends life

description: Archaeologists uncover a 2,000-year-old tomb beneath Petra's Treasury in Jordan, revealing 12 skeletons and well-preserved artifacts. Led by Dr. Pearce Paul Creasman, the team explores the significance of the burial site and its insights into Nabataean culture and history.
title: 2,000-year-old tomb with 12 skeletons discovered in Jordan

description: Ramiz Raja critiqued the exclusion of Babar Azam from the Test side, suggesting it was a hasty decision by new selectors. Pakistan's cricket team faces sponsorship challenges and declining star power after dropping key players for younger talents, following their loss to England.
title: 'He sells cricket for Pakistan...': Ramiz Raja on Babar Azam's Test axe

description: Chief Election Commissioner Rajiv Kumar rejects Congress's claims of EVM tampering in Haryana elections, asserting EVMs are foolproof. Despite exit polls favoring Congress, BJP won 48 seats, while Congress secured 37. EC also dismisses allegations of slow data uploading and manipulation.
title: '100% foolproof': How CEC responded to EVM tampering charge

description: A housekeeping staffer at a private Noida school was arrested for allegedly raping a three-year-old student on October 9. The young girl, identified the attacker, reported severe pain and injuries, prompting a police complaint and subsequent arrest. The school’s management is also being investigated.
title: 3-year-old raped in Noida school, housekeeping staffer held

description: The Reserve Bank of India may expand the RTGS to include major currencies like the US dollar, euro, and pound sterling. This move aims to make cross-border payments more affordable and faster.
title: RTGS transactions in dollar, pound and euros soon?

description: The Supreme Court rules that students with speech and language disabilities exceeding 40% should not be denied admission to medical colleges. Highlighting the necessity for inclusivity, the Court suggests that the National Medical Commission adopt a more accommodating approach, ensuring differently-abled individuals are integrated into mainstream society while examining potential breaches of equality laws.
title: Speech, language disabilities over 40% no bar to MBBS admissions: SC

description: Lawrence Bishnoi, a notorious gangster operating from prison, has a hit-list targeting prominent figures including Salman Khan and Zeeshan Siddique. Bishnoi's gang has been involved in high-profile assassinations and continues to expand its operations across multiple states, often recruiting vulnerable youth.
title: Who’s next? Unveiling Lawrence Bishnoi's notorious hit list of targets
‘Bishnoi gang linked to Indian govt agents’: Royal Canadian Mounted Police

description: In the 16th season of 'Kaun Banega Crorepati,' Amitabh Bachchan assists Prashant Pramod Jamdade from Sangli, Maharashtra, who aims to treat his disability and help his father. Amitabh offers to connect Prashant with hospitals in Mumbai, showcasing the show's emotional depth and intellectual engagement.
title: KBC16: Big B promises medical help to contestant, says 'I will...'

description: Eating speed significantly impacts health, with slow eating enhancing digestion and reducing overeating. Chewing food thoroughly can aid nutrient absorption. Rapid eating may spike blood sugar and elevate diabetes and obesity risks. Experts recommend mindful practices like moving meals to the dining area, counting chews, and taking small water sips between bites to foster healthier eating habits.
title: Slow eating vs fast eating: Everything you need to know

description: New Zealand will miss Kane Williamson for the India series opener as he recovers from a groin strain. Tom Latham takes over captaincy, and Mark Chapman may debut. Williamson's absence is significant given his experience, although his average in India is modest.
title: India vs New Zealand, 1st Test: The Kane Williamson void

description: Indian Test cricket captain Rohit Sharma has stated that Mohammed Shami's participation in the upcoming series against Australia remains uncertain due to a knee injury. Shami is currently receiving treatment at the National Cricket Academy and faces challenges in recovery with knee swelling issues.
title: Rohit Sharma gives a massive update on Mohammed Shami

description: A 28-year-old man from Hyderabad was beaten to death by a mob of 9-10 men in Malad East following a road rage incident involving an auto driver. The victim was attacked in front of bystanders who did not intervene, and police have arrested 9 suspects.
title: Mumbai road rage: Biker killed in front of family, 9 held

description: Monday Night Raw featured notable returns, high-stakes matches, and surprising victories. Rhea Ripley declared her intent to reclaim the Women's Championship, while Cody Rhodes faced Gunther ahead of their Crown Jewel match. Bianca Belair and Jade Cargill retained the Women's Tag Team titles. War Raiders returned to triumph in the Tag Team Championship Tournament.
title: WWE Raw results and highlights 10/14: Cody Rhodes, Gunther face-off and more

description: Hyundai IPO: Investors should consider holding Hyundai Motor India shares for at least a year to achieve substantial returns. Despite a modest listing predicted and a current grey market premium of Rs 30, analysts believe long-term gains are possible.
title: Hyundai IPO GMP crashes: Here’s what analysts recommend

description: Sanju Samson's swift century in the final T20I against Bangladesh, despite a tough start, highlights the Indian cricket team's supportive environment. Jitesh Sharma and Gautam Gambhir's remarks underline the team's emphasis on backing players and prioritizing national representation over individual competition, fostering a positive and encouraging atmosphere.
title: EXCLUSIVE | Backing Samson... gives hope to others: Jitesh Sharma

description: Nasa launched the Europa Clipper spacecraft to explore Jupiter's moon Europa, aiming to investigate its subsurface ocean for habitability. The mission, costing $5.2 billion, features nine instruments to study Europa's environment, expecting to reach Jupiter by 2030, and conduct 49 flybys over four years.
title: Nasa launches Europa Clipper to explore potential life on Jupiter's moon

description: North Korea has dismantled sections of inter-Korean roads on its side of the border, signaling a further deterioration in inter-Korean relations. This move, along with accusations against South Korea of flying drones over Pyongyang, heightens tensions and prompts military readiness between the two nations.
title: South Korea fires shots after North blows up roads: What’s behind escalation?

description: The first Test between India and New Zealand in Bengaluru may be interrupted by bad weather, with forecasts predicting rain and thunderstorms over the five days. India, leading the World Test Championship table, hopes to maintain momentum before heading to Australia for the Border Gavaskar Trophy.
title: India vs NZ: Rainy Bengaluru threatens 1st Test

description: Taiwan detected 153 Chinese military aircraft around its airspace in a single day, setting a record. The maneuvers occurred amid high tensions and followed China's large-scale military drills. Taiwan and the U.S. condemned the actions, while Japan expressed concerns. Taiwan's President vowed to protect the island's democracy and sovereignty.
title: Record 153 Chinese military aircraft fly around Taiwan airspace

description: HCLTech announces a 7% salary hike effective October 2024, with top performers receiving up to 15%, following an 11% rise in net profit for Q2, FY24. The hike is projected to have minimal impact on operating margins, while the company's headcount stands at 218,621.
title: HCL Tech announces salary hikes; how much top performers will get

description: The White House has issued a stern warning to Iran over threats against former President Donald Trump, emphasizing the severe consequences Tehran would face if any US citizen is targeted. National Security Council spokesperson Sean Savett highlighted the nation's commitment to protecting its citizens against any such aggression.
title: US warns Iran over threats against Trump, says monitoring for years

description: India's memorable two-wicket triumph over Australia in 1964 at Bombay's Brabourne Stadium, remembered for its collective determination, saw key performances from captain MAK Pataudi, Chandu Borde, and KS Indrajitsinhji. This historic win, cherished by cricket fans, was marked by a tense finish and enthusiastic fan celebrations.
title: Borde's heroics and India's unlikely victory over Australia in 1964

description: Government agencies in Delhi-NCR are implementing 27 measures under Grap Stage I to address worsening air quality. Steps include halting construction for unregistered projects, banning coal in tandoors, restricting diesel generators, and promoting eco-friendly practices. Authorities anticipate continued 'poor' air quality due to unfavorable weather conditions.
title: Delhi-NCR enters choke season? Grap-I enforced

description: The Election Commission is set to announce the dates for Maharashtra and Jharkhand elections, considering upcoming festivals. Polling might commence in mid-November to accommodate migrant voters. Bypolls for over 45 assembly seats and two Lok Sabha seats could align with these elections. Maharashtra's term ends on Nov 26, and Jharkhand's on Jan 5, 2025.
title: EC to announce poll dates for Maharashtra and Jharkhand today

description: Kamala Harris revealed an economic initiative, the 'Opportunity Agenda for Black men,' targeting Black business owners with forgivable loans and national marijuana legalization for economic inclusion. Aiming to regain Black male support before the November election, her agenda also covers cryptocurrency regulations, educational opportunities, and a health equity initiative.
title: Crypto, marijuana, forgiveable loans: Kamala Harris' outreach to black men

description: In Bigg Boss 18, intense drama unfolds as contestants assert themselves more. Avinash Mishra targets Shilpa Shirodkar during a task, sparking confrontations. Emotions run high with heated exchanges and emotional breakdowns among housemates like Eisha Singh and Alice Kaushik, leaving viewers intrigued by the evolving dynamics inside the house.
title: BB18: Avinash targets Shilpa during a task; the latter says 'Aap thodi...'

description: On October 15, 2024, people born under specific numerology numbers are influenced in various ways. Emphasis is placed on relationships, creativity, stability, and personal growth. Opportunities for emotional connections, professional recognition, and social engagements are highlighted. Challenges may include heightened sensitivity, communication issues, and the need for balance in personal and professional life.
title: Numerology predictions: Read your personalised forecast for numbers 1 to 9

description: Meta-owned social media platforms Facebook and Instagram experienced an outage affecting thousands worldwide. Users reported issues with login and receiving error messages, forcing many to turn to X for updates. The outage has since been resolved, but Meta has not disclosed the cause. Previous similar outages were also noted earlier this year.
title: Fb & Instagram outage: Services restored after disruption worldwide

description: Virat Kohli is working hard to improve his game against spin at the Chinnaswamy stadium, his home ground in the IPL. Despite recent struggles, head coach Gautam Gambhir supports him, emphasizing his consistency and hunger for success. Kohli is close to reaching the milestone of 9,000 Test runs, with more milestones in sight.
title: Virat Kohli eager to rediscover mojo against spin bowling

description: SpaceX has achieved a groundbreaking milestone by successfully catching its massive Super Heavy booster with launch tower arms for the first time. This accomplishment marks a significant step in SpaceX's quest to develop a fully reusable rocket system, crucial for NASA's lunar mission. Engineers hailed the event as historic, as the booster executed a flawless return.
title: SpaceX shares videos of giant metal arms catching rocket booster mid-air

description: Canadian PM Justin Trudeau talked with UK PM Keir Starmer amid escalating tensions with India over pro-Khalistan leader Nijjar's killing. Trudeau stressed Canada’s desire for cooperation with India. Meanwhile, India expelled Canadian diplomats, rejecting Canada's claims implicating Indian officials in Nijjar's death as politically motivated and aimed at vote bank politics.
title: Diplomatic row: Justin Trudeau discusses India with UK PM Keir Starmer

description: Congress leader Jairam Ramesh urged Prime Minister Modi to consult opposition parties on the critical issue of India-Canada relations amidst escalating diplomatic tensions. Both countries expelled diplomats following allegations linking Indian officials to criminal activities, further straining bilateral ties.
title: 'Hope PM Modi will ...': What Congress said on diplomatic fallout with Canada

description: Fakhar Zaman received a show-cause notice from the Pakistan Cricket Board for supporting Babar Azam after his exclusion from the Test squad. Former player Basit Ali praised but also warned Zaman of possible consequences from the Pakistan Cricket Board. Zaman had compared Babar's situation to Virat Kohli's lean phase for India.
title: 'Ladka bindaas hai, but...' - Pak batter Fakhar lauded & advised

description: Between Sept 15 and Oct 14, Haryana recorded 468 instances of farm fires during the paddy harvest season, the highest since 2020. Over 38.9 lakh acres produced an estimated 81 lakh tonnes of crop residue. Lack of accessible machinery and a dry season were significant factors contributing to the increase.
title: Haryana reports 468 farm fires in a month, highest since 2020

description: Nvidia's stock has surged, nearing record highs and positioning it to potentially overtake Apple as the world's most valuable company. Driven by intense AI competition among tech giants, Nvidia's market cap has reached $3.4 trillion, just behind Apple's $3.5 trillion. Analysts remain optimistic, setting a price target of $165.
title: Nvidia back to challenge Apple as world's most-valuable company

description: In a phased approach starting late October, African cheetahs brought to India will be released into the wild at Kuno National Park, Madhya Pradesh. Mixed pairs of male and female cheetahs will be released to prevent conflicts. The Gandhisagar Wildlife Sanctuary is also prepared to welcome a new batch of cheetahs as the second home in India.
title: Kuno Cheetahs likely to be back in wild by October-end

description: Chinese Premier Li Qiang's visit to Pakistan marks a significant event aimed at strengthening bilateral trade and economic relations, amid heightened security following recent attacks on Chinese nationals. His virtual inauguration of Gwadar airport highlights ongoing challenges. The visit coincides with the SCO summit, involving high-level regional diplomacy and security measures in Islamabad.
title: Islamabad 'lockdown' greets Chinese PM amid aftershocks of Karachi suicide attack

description: An Indian-Russian working group met in New Delhi on Oct 10 to discuss cooperation in the Northern Sea Route, focusing on polar navigation, Arctic shipbuilding projects, and training Indian sailors. They also drafted a memorandum for cargo shipping collaboration between the countries.
title: India-Russia working group discusses steps on Arctic shipbuilding, sailor training

description: Pakistan women's team met a dismal fate in their T20 World Cup match against New Zealand, getting dismissed for just 56 while chasing a modest 110. Despite restrictive bowling, poor shot selection and dropped catches contributed to their downfall, leading to criticism from ex-players and experts, including Basit Ali who lashed out on the team in his analysis.
title: 'Pak women cricket team played badminton like its chairperson'

description: Power, a two-year-old doberman, significantly aided police by leading them to a crucial piece of evidence in a gang-rape investigation near Surat. Her tracking abilities pinpointed a motorcycle connected to the suspects, resulting in the arrest of three individuals involved in the crime.
title: Gujarat: 'Power' cuts gangrape accused’s run short

description: Murari Lal Kushwaha, a tea seller from Shivpuri, Madhya Pradesh, spent Rs 60,000 on a lavish celebration that included a DJ procession and a JCB hoisting, to mark the purchase of a moped. Police seized the DJ equipment and charged him for noise pollution. This extravagant gesture was meant to bring joy to his children.
title: MP tea seller throws lavish DJ procession to celebrate new ride

description: Ram Gopal Mishra, 22, was killed during clashes linked to a Durga Puja procession in Lucknow. A video shows Mishra on a house, removing a green flag and waving a saffron one, before being shot. Police are investigating the video's authenticity as part of the ongoing probe into the violent outbreak sparked by conflicting celebrations and prayer times.
title: Bahraich clashes: How unrest began at Maharajganj Bazar during Durga Puja procession

description: In Siddipet district's Wargal mandal, frustrated villagers cut down over 25 trees without permission to expedite a delayed road-widening project. The trees were part of the Haritha Haram initiative. Authorities are currently assessing the damage and potential penalties.
title: Long wait for pucca road: Telangana villagers cut down 25 trees
